ortlessly price      reviews more options »  per page  per page  per page area rugs buying guide shopping for an area rug can be overwhelming especially when buying online—so we’re here to help make your search easier think of this guide as your starting point to answer the tough questions and help you find the size quality and style of area rug that’s the best fit for your space not sure about what size is right for your space or what look you want to achieve well help you every step of the waythe rug buying questions you should be asking are found out more about whats the right size whats the best quality what look do you want what are the care details whats the right size the size of your space and furniture layout are the two main considerations when choosing a area rug size avoid the common mistake of buying a throw rug that’s too small—if you’re unsure or between sizes err on the larger side for a final look that feels thoughtful instead of haphazard living area there are three common furniture arrangements that impact the size you should get the rug should always be grounded under your coffee table and the right dimensions determined from there based on the layout you want all legs on the rug front legs on the rug coffee table on the rug an alllegson layout is the best choice for anchoring open concept spaces and will require the largest area rug frontlegson is the most versatile and onlycoffeetableon is ideal for small spaces keep uniformity across all your furniture pieces so if only the front legs of your sofa are on the rug the same goes for your armchairs and side tables too dining room simply add  inches to both the length and width of your table—or to the diameter if it’s round be sure to pull the leaves of your table out if you use them regularly when entertaining this rule prevents chairs from sitting on uneven surfaces or catching the edge of a rug as they’re pushed in all legs on the rug all legs on the rug bedroom use your bed as the sizing guide for the three main layout options the rug should always extend  inches beyond all sides of the bed all legs on the rug  bed on the rug runners on each side when determining size account for any furniture at the foot of the bed—the entire piece should either sit on or off the area or throw rug if you have nightstands measure the distance from the outer edges to find the right width for runners the width should be larger than your nightstands but slightly shorter than the length of your bed kitchen for rooms with an island or galley layout a runner can visually extend the space hallway runners are the goto choice for corridors where it’s best not to have any furniture legs sit on the rug entry let the shape of the space dictate the choice of round rectangular or runner and use the width of your front door as a baseline check the pile height to ensure your door will clear the throw rug when it’s opened what qualities matter to you how a rug is made and the material it’s made with will determine the key qualities of the rug like durability and softness the best combination of the two depends on what’s important to you in the space you’re shopping for holds up to high traffic wool flat weavefibers are woven together into a thin matlike area rug knottedfibers are tied in individual knots ideal wool has resilient fibers that spring back standing up to wear flat weave or knotted styles in cotton or synthetic materials are durable easy to clean and may be reversible avoid shag or highpile rugs will flatten especially in synthetic materials silk is too delicate to stand up to wear and jute or sisal stain very easily stands up to stains cotton synthetic or wool low to no pilepile the density of the fibers in a rug pile height is the thickness and ranges from flat  inch to thick  inch ideal cotton and synthetic materials are very easy to clean and cotton is often machine washable wool is naturally stain resistant lowpile weaves are the easiest to spot treat avoid jute and sisal can irreversibly stain some pets can be allergic to jute can handle moisture synthetic materials wool in flatwoven stylesfibers are woven together into a thin matlike rug ideal silk and jute are moisture sensitive and a high pile will absorb humidity avoid jute and sisal can irreversibly stain some pets can be allergic to jute lasts for decades wool handmade the gold standard that creates strong longlasting rugs ideal handmade rugs in wool especially handknotted or handtufted are the best—though they’re more expensive shorter pile heights will wear better over time avoid cotton and synthetic materials in machinemade styles are better shortterm options high pile throw rugs are likely to matte or dent what look do you want choosing a rug is a matter of taste—there’s no right or wrong choice but if you’re not sure what style you want here’s how you can think about it neutral room statement rug photo natalie myers if you want your rug to be the statement piece in a room with mostly solid colored furniture or a subtle overall palette consider a highcontrast pattern bold geometric prints bright kilims orientals with lots of detail or overdyed persians can be the star of the show choosing a rug is a matter of taste—there’s no right or wrong choice but if you’re not sure what style you want here’s how you can think about it neutral room quiet rug photo victoria elizabeth design if you like your neutral or monochromatic room the way it is and want your rug to follow suit look for a rug in the same color palette that features a subtle pattern or texture natural fiber rugs like jute and sisal are also a great option bold room quiet rug photo a place of my taste you’ve got two options a solid neutralcolor or naturalfiber area rug are great options for keeping it simple or choose a solid throw rug in the secondary color of your room’s palette for a cohesive look bold room statement rug photo chango  co if you have a dramatic style go all in with the rug you love if you already have pattern in your room keep the scale rule in mind any new print you introduce should be four times bigger or smaller than the others so as not to compete with or overwhelm your existing look not sure photo common bond design that’s ok stick with the standbys stripes solid color or jute rugs think of it as a starter rug and look for simple more affordable options the care details here’s what you should know before purchasing machinewashable vs professional cleaning most cotton rugs can be machinewashed wool silk hides and natural fiber rugs should be professionally cleaned some rugs can only be spotcleaned frequency its important to deepclean rugs every  months vacuuming all rugs regardless of material can and should be vacuumed regularly without the brush roll on to keep from damaging the fibers jute and sisal rugs should be vacuumed frequently because of their loose weave tufted wool rugs should be vacuumed frequently especially early on as they shed delicate or highpile rugs can be shaken out and brushed to clean related searches hallway runner rugs x area rugs shaggy area rugs kitchen rugs teal area rug turquoise area rug sponsored links get it fast express shipping zip code   change rug size  x   x   x   x   x   x   x   x   x   x     roundsquare    roundsquare    roundsquare    roundsquare  runner  runner  runner  runner   runner sample color price per item under   to   to   to   to    above  to  material wool synthetics polypropylene polyester cotton jute  sisal silk natural fibers leather cowhide chenille bamboo rayon  seagrass sheepskin microfiber pile height flat  thin  medium  thick  rug shape rectangle runner round square oval octagon novelty half circle primary pattern geometric oriental floral  plants solid trellis abstract striped color bordered chevron tibetan ikat southwestern animal print plaid paisley polka dots camouflage recommended use indoor indooroutdoor features floor heating safe ecofriendly reversible nonslip backing special offers sale